				<li id="16671940" class="cmnt-root" data="2" data-d="1651872953000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579137/Lightning-Strike" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 May 2022 17:35</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16671940" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Great in PvP. Good range and damage and chainable. Bolts are kinda random so you might hit or might not, but then again from your opponent&apos;s perspective they might dodge or they might not. The risk of this randomness is mitigated because you can use it at a safe range. I like to punish rolls towards me with catch flame, then when they roll away I beast sling --&gt; chain into lightning strike. Then I can chain into other spells like triple-rings to keep the pressure up at midrange.<br/><br/>Especially good in Liurnia because water.<br/><br/>Elaboration about why this can be hard to dodge in PvP: your i-frames are what you see on _your_ screen, but your position is what your opponent sees on _their_ screen. With latency, this means you shouldn&apos;t dodge the bolt which is about to strike where you are now, you need to dodge the bolt which is about to strike where your position was 0.5 seconds ago. This is difficult to judge in the heat of battle.<br/><br/>This spell is balanced by its stamina and fp cost, but is still excellent in many situations. You can get it very early too. I didn&apos;t even mention PvE (great for big enemies and groups).</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16671940" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16671940" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16671940"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16671940" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16671940"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
